Name: Description
Student Racial/Ethnic Diversity by Chart:
Diversity refers to the racial/ethnic makeup of students at middle schools within a specific geography, using the DOE's categories of Asian, Black, Hispanic, White, and Multiple Race Categories Not Represented. School diversity is determined in the following way:
- Diverse (No one group exceeds 50 percent and no two groups exceed 80 percent);
- Predominantly White (White students make up 50+ percent and no other group exceeds 20 percent);
- Predominantly Asian (Asian students make up 50+ percent and no other group exceeds 20 percent);
- Predominantly White + Asian (White and Asian students make up 80+ percent combined);
- Predominantly Black (Black students make up 50+ percent and no other group exceeds 20 percent);
- Predominantly Hispanic (Hispanic students make up 50+ percent and no other group exceeds 20 percent);
- Predominantly Black + Hispanic (Black and Hispanic students make up 80+ percent combined).

Name: Source Notes
Student Racial/Ethnic Diversity by Chart: CCC analysis of New York City Department of Education, Demographic Snapshots (School Year 2018-19, 2019-20); retrieved from https://infohub.nyced.org/reports-and-policies/citywide-information-and-data/information-and-data-overview

Name: Notes
Student Racial/Ethnic Diversity by Chart: Counts and percentages account for all levels of instruction in charter schools only.
